+            # Upstream used `replace(..., "".join(rendered_images), 1)`
+            # which puts the full concatenation into the first <image>
+            # and leaves the remaining N-1 <image> tokens as stray
+            # placeholders — for 6-frame video that adds 5 extra
+            # placeholder tokens (1541 total instead of the 1536
+            # features mlx_vlm's vision tower produces), and
+            # _merge_features ValueErrors. Per-placeholder replacement
+            # gives exact token=feature alignment for multi-image input.
+            for r in rendered_images:
